A dormitory at the Bungoma High School was destroyed by fireÂ  Friday morning. The incident brings to seven the number of learning institutions that have lost property through fire in the county this week. Others are Chesamisi High School, Kimilili High School, Bukembe Boys, Ndivisi High School, Mbakalu High School and Khasoko High School. The cause of the fire at Bungoma High's Muliro dormitory is still unknown. The police have launched investigations. The fire started when students were in class for preps. Bungoma high school principal Godfrey Awuori declined to comment on the matter. The students were not sent home by the school board of management. 